1. Živo me interesuje tvoj novi posao. (I am *very* interested in your new job.)
2. Moja baka je *živo* nervozna kada dolazim kasno kući. (My grandma gets *extremely* nervous when I come home late.)
3. Živeći u malom gradu, često mi nedostaju *živa* dešavanja. (Living in a small town, I often miss *lively* events.)
4. Njihova muzika je *živo* svirana, što privlači veliki broj ljudi. (Their music is *vividly* played, which attracts a large number of people.)
5. *Živo* mi je žao što nisam mogao da prisustvujem tvojoj svadbi. (I am *deeply* sorry that I couldn't attend your wedding.)
6. U toku leta, grad postaje *živ* i prepun turista. (During the summer, the city becomes *alive* and full of tourists.)
7. *Živo* me zanima tvoje mišljenje o ovoj knjizi. (I am *keenly* interested in your opinion about this book.)
8. Njegovo izlaganje je bilo *živo* i zabavno, što je publiku držalo angažovanom. (His presentation was *vibrant* and entertaining, which kept the audience engaged.)
9. Kada sam video taj prizor, *živo* sam se uplašio. (When I saw that scene, I was *thoroughly* frightened.)
10. Na ovoj slici, boje su *živo* prikazane i čine je veoma privlačnom. (In this picture, the colors are *vividly* depicted and make it very attractive.)